<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<I c="LootActions" i="action" m="interactions.utils.loot" n="loot_EP20World_NPCs_TownGossip" s="456365">
  <L n="loot_actions">
    <V t="notification_and_dialog">
      <U n="notification_and_dialog">
        <V n="dialog" t="notification">
          <U n="notification">
            <L n="dialog_options">
              <E>DISABLE_CLOSE_BUTTON</E>
            </L>
            <V n="icon" t="enabled">
              <V n="enabled" t="participant">
                <U n="participant">
                  <L n="participant_type">
                    <E>TargetSim</E>
                  </L>
                </U>
              </V>
            </V>
            <V n="secondary_icon" t="enabled">
              <V n="enabled" t="participant">
                <U n="participant">
                  <L n="participant_type">
                    <E>Actor</E>
                  </L>
                </U>
              </V>
            </V>
            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0x5F8FD325<!--String: "Camp Gibbi Gibbi has been a fixture of Gibbi Point for many decades! It was founded by one of the early adventurers and was initially just a small series of canvas tents that absolutely no one wanted to sleep in whatsoever. Now it's expanded into a more hospitable location and is a go-to for any kid looking for a little outdoor fun."--></T>
                  <T>0x6C1A0A31<!--String: "You've probably heard a little about the history of Plumbirds already, because they're just such a fixture here even if the small ones are rather shy these days. Back when we used to see far more Plumbirds, they loved to gather out near where the Lonely Lighthouse is in that peninsula in Jellyfish Junction. Apparently they loved watching ships come in. The area became littered with Plumbird feathers, which locals began using for their arrow fletching."--></T>
                  <T>0xDABD4D22<!--String: "The Lonely Lighthouse has been perched at the edge of Fletcher's Point for many generations, dating back to when Jellyfish Junction was more of a destination for fishing boats and ships alike. It has become an odd sort of message board for a few Sims who like to put up notes to see if anyone will reply. "--></T>
                  <T>0xDFB2CB11<!--String: "Crystal Valley used to be more of a gold mining operation! It's true! The mine there, Scoop's Mine, was primarily used for gold mining until one day when there was a particularly, er, vibrant geyser blow from Hothead Rock Geyser made it suddenly produce crystals! The Scoop Family has largely moved on these days as a consequence, and those who remain are quite reclusive. However, Buddy Scoop can still be found running his little collectible stand near the old mine entrance in Crystal Valley. That little rapscallion used to sneak into the mines for more treasure, so we had to board it up."--></T>
                  <T>0x33E4D593<!--String: "The Old Firewatch Tower was established years ago when fire danger was more of an issue in Wanderwood Wilds. These days, things are a bit more under control in the neighborhood. Nevertheless, a Hermit Ranger still resides at the top. Don't try to go up—they won't let you! And the Ranger never comes down, either, though they do appreciate hearing from the outside world from time to time so feel free to stop by and send up a note to them or maybe even drop off a gift if you're feeling bold."--></T>
                  <T>0x67400136<!--String: "The Electric Lagoon was once a cenote, you know! I bet it was truly spectacular to behold back in the day. But one day, a large geyser blast shook the whole neighborhood to such an extent that the cenote collapsed, leaving the walls behind. It's still rather lovely and honestly, I think having a backdrop of the stars above you makes it even more glorious to behold. You can catch jellyfish in it if you're up for fishing, but it also makes for a lovely kayaking spot."--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
            <V n="title" t="enabled">
              <T n="enabled">0x4C1EBF1A<!--String: "Storyteller's Lore"--></T>
            </V>
            <E n="visual_type">SPEECH</E>
          </U>
        </V>
      </U>
    </V>
  </L>
